title: "DRMYN Studio: A Metadata-Only Human-Agent Film Production Workflow"
type: software
version: 0.3.1
date-released: 2026-05-06
repository-code: "https://github.com/hknbb/drmyn-studio-public"
url: "https://github.com/hknbb/drmyn-studio-public/releases/tag/v0.3.1"
abstract: >
  DRMYN Studio is a metadata-only, schema-validated, human-gated pre-production
  and prompt governance pipeline for AI-assisted film production. It provides
  scene cards, character and location records, continuity files, prompt
  lifecycle infrastructure, JSON schema validation (20+ schemas, draft 2020-12),
  a three-agent autonomous orchestration layer (Claude Code / Codex / Gemini
  Code Assist) with auto-handoff and pickup mode enabling structured multi-agent
  coordination without external APIs, a Streamlit dashboard for operator
  oversight, and a Film Aesthetic Bible system that injects deterministic,
  scene-grounded visual keywords into T2I prompts via named aesthetic packs.
  All production decisions are reproducible and academically defensible;
  generated media outputs are stored externally and referenced by metadata-only
  records. Demonstrated through the Closing Price AI-assisted film project.
keywords:
